$interpreted: Clark: This casino is huge! Where do we begin?
Joan: Woah, woah, woah~ This requires finesse.
Rune: Finesse?
Clark: Don't move! We don't want to attract the attention of the guards.
Joan: (Did he grab my hand on purpose? I wonder if he likes me...)
Joan: (...ah, what a shame. I don't like guys that wear glasses. I've made him fall for me. Alas! What kind of woman am I?)
Sophie: Joan, what did you mean?
Joan: Tenth rule of being a thief: When you come across a difficult obstacle, grab a coward and interrogate him!
Clark: Coward? They won't have "coward" written on their forehead. How do we know who's a coward?
Sophie: That huge crab!!??
Joan: No, not him you dummy. Look closely.
Jahan: Welcome...to the Oasis Casino~
Chief Guard: Is your waist made of wood? Bend down further you mutt!!
Chief Guard: Plus, you're too quiet! Louder!!
Jahan: Yes, yes, yes, sir~ WELCOME TO THE OASIS CASINO!
Chief Guard: Not that loud, you dumb face. But much better.
Jahan: Thank you for your pointers, sir.
Jahan: Hmph! If we were in the Kingdom of the Sun, I'd have enough people under me to have your butt pummelled in!!...*spit*...
Joan: Take that!
Jahan: What's going on...
Rune: Speak!
Jahan: Ouch!! I'll talk, I'll talk! Please, don't hit me! But if you do, just don't hit my face. I rely on my beauty to get by~
Clark: *tsk*...*tsk*...perhaps we've chosen too hastily?
Joan: Where's my master?
Sophie: Where's the secret room?
Jahan: Secret room!? I don't know who your master is!
Sophie: Answer my questions!
Joan: No, first answer my──
Clark: If we wait for you two, it's going to be dark before we finish. How about I give it a try - -
Clark: The top prize at the casino and the High Priest's secret room; where are they?
Jahan: They're in the same place. That fat bird is in Devious' room.
Sophie: Now I see~ Devious is the one pulling the strings here at the Oasis Casino.
Jahan: That place is heavily guarded. I strongly advise you not to try anything stupid...
Jahan: Unless...
